If f \colon  A \to  B is compatible with W, F, and \overline {F}, then we have

523Equationhodge-theory-ii-equation-1.2.10.1hodge-theory-ii-equation-1.2.10.1.xml1.2.10.1hodge-theory-ii-1.2       f(A_i^{p,q})        \subset  B_i^{p,q}        \qquad \text {for }i=0,1.     \tag{1.2.10.1}     

Claim (iii) then follows from the following lemma:

The A_i^{p,q} give a bigrading of A.
We have

